Our school still uses stickers on vehicles as a gatepass. Something that is very old fashioned and unfashionable for vehicles. But more importantly, can be a security issue. 

If there was a way to allow the campus cctv pointed at the gate to check if the car is allowed to enter the campus or not.

There is! a simple database check, and image-processing/ computer vision should solve this


To try the project, simply run python pipeline.py [insert how to install deps]


Notes:

Inconsistent lighting and angles affect accuracy of OCR. In the actual setting of this project, the cctv is at a fixed angle, and lighting will only varied by time of the day and the gate's artificial lighting.